msgid "Fine Tuning The Rotation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:78
msgid ""
":doc:`Precise control "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/precision>` can be had over "
"rotation through the use of the :kbd:`Shift` and :kbd:`Ctrl` keys to limit "
"rotation to discrete amounts. You can also enter a :doc:`numerical value "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/numeric_input>` in degrees to "
"specify the amount of rotation after after initiating a rotation "
"transformation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:84
msgid ""
"Hold :kbd:`Ctrl` down while performing a rotation to rotate the selected "
"element in 5 degree increments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:85
msgid ""
"Hold :kbd:`Shift` down while performing a rotation to rotate the selected "
"element in 0.01 degree increments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:86
msgid ""
"Hold :kbd:`Shift-Ctrl` down while performing a rotation to rotate the "
"selected element in 1 degree increments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:87
msgid "Press :kbd:`R`, type in a number and press :kbd:`Return` to confirm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:88
msgid "Press :kbd:`R`, :kbd:`R` to enable Trackball rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:91
msgid "Orientation dependant rotations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/rotate.rst:93
msgid ""
"By default, all rotations happen around a Global Orientation. You can change"
" the rotation orientation by pressing the axis key twice. For example, "
"pressing :kbd:`R`, :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`X` will by default set rotation to occur "
"around the local orientation."
msgstr ""

